The paper deals with the calibration of depth cameras for mobile robots, which is a common problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The calibration is done using a probabilistic approach, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.CV, cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a second range sensor, which is a common technique in robotics for improving accuracy (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a method that can be easily executed by mobile robotic platforms, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
